This paper belongs to the field of online social network research, which is a multidisciplinary field that can be categorized into several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis of social networks and their properties. The second likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), which focuses on the study of social phenomena and human behavior using computational methods. The third likely sub-category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), which deals with the security and privacy issues in online social networks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DL (Machine Learning), which can be relevant if the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the social network data. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which can be relevant if the paper uses information retrieval techniques to analyze the social network data.
